## Read first (rules)
- [Small PRs, one concern each](feedback_small_prs.md) — owner rejects multi-concern PRs; split before opening, never bundle "while I was here" fixes.
- [Client-side state is not a concurrency guard](feedback_example.md) — double-submit created a duplicate payment; synchronous ref + server-side idempotency key on every money move.
- [Absolute dates in all notes and memories](feedback_absolute_dates.md) — "last Tuesday" is meaningless in three months.

## External API pitfalls
- [PayVendor wraps everything in a double data envelope](reference_example.md) — actual payload at `response.data.data`; statuses UPPERCASE, lowercase before DB insert.
- [PayVendor sandbox rejects enum values its docs list](reference_payvendor_enum_validation.md) — validate against the live sandbox before changing wire data.

